Lucky implings are a type of impling that can be caught in the Impetuous Impulses minigame, and are located throughout Puro-Puro and Gielinor. Players need at least 89 Hunter to capture this type of impling with a butterfly net or a magic butterfly net, or 99 Hunter to capture it barehanded.

Loot[edit | edit source]

Main article: Treasure Trails § Rewards

Looting a lucky impling gives players one roll on the drop table of an easy, medium, hard, elite, or master clue scroll. There is an equal chance of rolling into each tier's clue scroll table.[1]

At current Grand Exchange prices, catching a lucky impling gives 56,385 coins worth of loot, on average.

There is also a chance of obtaining a clue scroll as a tertiary drop when catching a lucky impling.

The following drop rates are provided by Jagex, unless otherwise specified.

Rarity[edit | edit source]

The chance of a Lucky impling spawning in Puro-Puro is 1/301. In Gielinor, the spawn rate is 1/101.[2] These rates make the Lucky impling about nine times rarer than a Dragon impling in Puro-Puro, and ten times rarer in Gielinor.

References[edit | edit source]

  1. ^ Jagex. Mod Ash's Twitter account. 1 October 2016. (Archived from the original on 8 August 2019.) Mod Ash: "It rolls the easy, medium, hard, elite or master clue lists with equal chance of each."
  2. ^ Jagex. Mod Ash's Twitter account. 13 May 2017. (Archived from the original on 8 August 2019.) Mod Ash: "1/101, or 1/301 in the maze."
